HEADWORD: Doni
<hw>Do"ni</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Tamil
<ets>t<?/n⟦imac⟧</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A clumsy craft,
having one mast with a long sail, used for trading purposes on the
coasts of Coromandel and Ceylon.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>dhony</asp>, <asp>doney</asp>, and <asp>done</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Balfour.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
